    <h1>Managing payments</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page of the manual describes and explains how to manage payments. You receive payments in your system from different sources. Independent of the payment source, you can manage all incoming payments in the <strong>Orders » Payments</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="basic-settings">1. Carrying out basic settings for incoming payments</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, carry out basic settings for automatically assigning payments to orders and for giving goodwill on payments. Default settings are already saved in the system. These default values are generally recommended. To change these settings, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Changing the basic settings:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Payment » Incoming</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to the information given in <a href="#table-manually-booking-payments">Table 3</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
